4.  Climate change sector specialists (5 specialists, 3 person-months each, for a total of 15 
person-months, intermittent). At least five specialists will undertake the sector analyses (agriculture; 
forest; water; marine and coastal resources, including fisheries; and health) at the country and 
regional levels. Each specialist will have extensive knowledge on climate change for the assigned 
sector. A minimum of 5 years work experience with a master’s degree in a specific sector are 
required. The successful candidate will 
(i)  review  current  and  existing  studies  on  climate  change  adaptation  options  and 
practices for that sector;  
(ii)  review and analyze the existing regional sector-specific policies and policy gaps; 
(iii)  identify possible options and practices for reducing GHGs in the sector as an input 
to modeling abatement strategies for a low carbon economy;   
(iv)  identify climate change impacts and possible adaptation options and practices in the 
sector as an input to modeling and/or assessment of climate change impacts;  
(v)  formulate sector-specific adaptation options;  
(vi)  prepare and submit a report on the above items; and 
(vii)  perform other tasks relevant to this TA as may be assigned by the team leader and 
the lead consultant. 

B.  National Consultants 

5.  National climate experts (8 specialists, 4 person-months each, for a total of 32 person-
months, intermittent). At least eight national climate experts (two for each participating country) will 
undertake  country-level  review,  assessment,  data  gathering,  and  administrative  support.  A 
minimum of 5 years work experience with a master’s degree in climate change fields are required. 
